      <notesStmt>
        <note>Title from colophon (f. 5r).</note>
        <note>Written in 8 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>5 leaves foliated 1-5, upper left and lower right verso.</note>
        <note>Dated śaka 1786 and saṃvat 1921 (1864) (f. 5r).</note>
        <note>Mistakes blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins.</note>
        <note>Written on blue, European stock of paper with the watermark name of "Millington" a possible reference to the company C. Millington &amp; Son known to distribute paper in South Asia; there is also a partial date of -862 (equals 1862) on one of the folios.</note>
      </notesStmt>
